---
/**
 * Multi-model / cross-model coordination section.
 *
 * The differentiator: CTXone is the only system where Claude, GPT,
 * Gemini, a local Ollama model, and a Python script can all share
 * the same memory graph and plan — with no glue code, no custom
 * orchestration layer, no framework lock-in.
 *
 * The model doesn't hold the state. The system does. That's what
 * makes true multi-model coordination possible without code.
 */
---

<section class="section multimodel">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="eyebrow">
			<span class="eyebrow-text">MULTI-MODEL //</span>
		</div>

		<div class="layout">
			<div class="copy">
				<h2>One memory graph.<br />Every model you use.</h2>
				<p class="lede">
					Most teams don't use one AI tool. They use Claude for
					complex reasoning, a local model for routine work,
					Gemini for search-grounded tasks. Each one starts
					every session knowing nothing about the others.
				</p>
				<p class="lede">
					CTXone is the shared context layer they all draw from —
					no glue code, no custom orchestration, no framework
					lock-in. Claude remembers a decision. Cursor picks it
					up. A Python script acts on it. They're all working
					from the same plan, the same memory, the same branch.
				</p>
				<ul class="claims">
					<li>
						<span class="claim-dot"></span>
						Any MCP-capable tool reads and writes the same graph
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="claim-dot"></span>
						Plans are model-agnostic — any agent picks up the next task
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="claim-dot"></span>
						No orchestration code required — coordination happens through shared state
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="claim-dot"></span>
						Switch models mid-project — context follows, not the model
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="diagram">
				<div class="hub">
					<div class="hub-label">CTXone Hub</div>
					<div class="hub-sub">memory · plans · branches</div>
				</div>

				<div class="spokes">
					<div class="spoke spoke-1">
						<div class="spoke-line"></div>
						<div class="spoke-node">Claude Code</div>
					</div>
					<div class="spoke spoke-2">
						<div class="spoke-line"></div>
						<div class="spoke-node">Cursor</div>
					</div>
					<div class="spoke spoke-3">
						<div class="spoke-line"></div>
						<div class="spoke-node">Gemini</div>
					</div>
					<div class="spoke spoke-4">
						<div class="spoke-line"></div>
						<div class="spoke-node">Local model</div>
					</div>
					<div class="spoke spoke-5">
						<div class="spoke-line"></div>
						<div class="spoke-node">Python script</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="diagram-note">
					All agents. Same memory graph. Same plan. No code connecting them.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.multimodel {
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				ellipse 70% 50% at 50% 50%,
				rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.06),
				transparent 65%
			),
			var(--ctx-bg);
		border-top: 1px solid var(--ctx-border-lo);
	}

	.eyebrow {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
		background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08);
		border: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.28);
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--ctx-accent);
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.layout {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 4rem;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.copy h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
		font-weight: 800;
		color: #ffffff;
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
		line-height: 1.1;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.copy h2 br {
		display: block;
	}

	.lede {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		line-height: 1.65;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		max-width: 36rem;
	}

	.claims {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 1.5rem 0 0 0;
		padding: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.7rem;
	}

	.claims li {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-start;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		font-size: 0.88rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		line-height: 1.45;
	}

	.claim-dot {
		flex-shrink: 0;
		width: 6px;
		height: 6px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: var(--ctx-accent);
		box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.6);
		margin-top: 0.45rem;
	}

	/* Hub-and-spokes diagram */
	.diagram {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0;
	}

	.hub {
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.45);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
		padding: 1rem 1.75rem;
		text-align: center;
		box-shadow:
			0 0 0 4px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.06),
			0 0 24px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.12);
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
	}

	.hub-label {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--ctx-accent);
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
	}

	.hub-sub {
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		margin-top: 0.2rem;
	}

	.spokes {
		display: flex;
		gap: 0.6rem;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		justify-content: center;
		margin-top: 1.25rem;
	}

	.spoke {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.4rem;
	}

	.spoke-line {
		width: 1px;
		height: 1.5rem;
		background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.4), rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1));
	}

	.spoke-node {
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-md);
		padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.diagram-note {
		margin-top: 1.25rem;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		text-align: center;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-style: italic;
	}

	@media (max-width: 860px) {
		.layout {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2.5rem;
		}
	}
</style>
